        "text": "The Helvetii had persuaded the Tulingi, the Latovici, the Rauraci, and the Boii to join in their migration. The Aedui sent envoys to Caesar to entreat assistance, as did the Ambarri, who were friends and kinsmen of the Aedui. Caesar found that Dumnorix, the brother of Divitiacus, had been the chief author of the embassy to the Helvetii on the part of the Aedui, although he openly professed himself a friend of Rome."
